I always change my mind.
I'll get your hot chocolate.

231
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:29,537
I don't want any,
thank you.
Will that be all then?

232
00:17:29,615 --> 00:17:31,583
Mm-hmm.
Very good, miss.

233
00:17:33,819 --> 00:17:38,779
Do you think if one makes up
one's mind about doing something
that really helps one to do it?

234
00:17:38,857 --> 00:17:42,554
Indubitably, miss.
I made up my mind that I like
this house and everybody in it.

235
00:17:42,628 --> 00:17:45,756
- And everybody in it's
going to like me.
- Cheerful thought, miss.

236
00:17:45,831 --> 00:17:49,699
They didn't have to have me
come live with them if they
didn't want me.
No, miss.

237
00:17:49,768 --> 00:17:53,067
UncleJim asked me to come.
So Mrs. Clinton
told me.

238
00:17:53,138 --> 00:17:57,006
Don't you ever smile?
I'm sorry, miss,
but if I may say so,

239
